== Partial sets ==
In addition to the full sets above, there are a few sets that consist of only a few pieces.

* '''Bar''': Consists of the {{item|Bar|link=Table}}, {{item|Bar Stool}}, and arguably {{item|Banquet Table}}. Crafted with [[Any Wood]] at a [[Sawmill]].
* '''Jack 'O Lantern''': Consists of the {{item|Jack 'O Lantern}}, {{item|Hanging Jack 'O Lantern}}, and {{item|Jackelier}}. Crafted from [[Pumpkin]]s at a [[Work Bench]].

== Individual items ==
There are also individual items that do not fit into one of the above sets but are of the above item types.

* '''Chests''': Apart from the [[Chests]] listed in above sets, some Chests are only found naturally and are not part of a furniture set. Most contain unique treasures for their type.
** The {{item|Gold Chest}} is found in the [[Underground]] in [[Underground Cabin]]s and is also found in locked form in the [[Dungeon]].
** The {{item|Ivy Chest}} is found in the [[Underground Jungle]] in [[Jungle Shrine]]s and [[Living Mahogany Tree]]s.
** The {{item|Web Covered Chest}} is found in [[Spider Nest]]s.
** The {{item|Shadow Chest}} is found in the [[Underworld]], usually in [[Ruined houses]] in locked form originally.
** The {{nowrap|{{item|mode=image|Jungle Chest}}{{item|mode=image|Corruption Chest}}{{item|mode=image|Crimson Chest}}{{item|mode=image|Hallowed Chest}}{{item|mode=image|Ice Chest}}{{item|mode=image|Desert Chest}} [[Biome Chests]]}} are found in the Dungeon.
* '''Doors''': In addition to the [[Doors]] listed above, there are two other Doors that are not part of any set.
** {{item|Iron Door}} 
** {{item|Lead Door}}.
* '''Dungeon''': In addition to the four main sets (one found in each color of the Dungeon and the Gothic set), every Dungeon can also contain additional furniture.
** '''Doors''': The {{item|Dungeon Door}}.
** '''Platforms''': The {{item|Dungeon Shelf}}, {{item|Brass Shelf}}, {{item|Metal Shelf}}, and {{item|Wood Shelf}}.
** '''Lanterns''': The {{item|Chain Lantern}}, {{item|Brass Lantern}}, {{item|Caged Lantern}}, {{item|Carriage Lantern}}, {{item|Alchemy Lantern}}, {{item|Diabolist Lamp}}, and {{item|Oil Rag Sconse}}.
* '''Platforms''': In addition to the [[platforms]] listed above, and the platforms found in the Dungeon, some more types exist.
** {{nowrap|{{item|mode=image|id=3622}}{{item|mode=image|id=3638}}{{item|mode=image|id=3639}}{{item|mode=image|id=3640}}{{item|mode=image|id=3641}}{{item|mode=image|id=3642}} [[Team Platforms]],}} which are randomly sold by the [[Traveling Merchant]] for {{iteminfo|3622|buy}} each.
** {{item|mode=image|Echo Platform}} [[Echo Platform|Echo Platforms]], which are completely invisible when placed and can only be seen by having [[Spectre Goggles]] equipped or being near an [[Echo Chamber]].
* '''Other light sources''': These [[light sources]] do not fit into a set, but some provide unique effects. Others are purely decorative.
** '''Buff lanterns''': These [[lanterns]] provide regeneration [[buffs]] within an area around them when placed.
*** The {{item|Heart Lantern}} provides a [[health regeneration]] buff and is crafted with a [[Life Crystal]] and 4 [[Chain]]s.
*** The {{item|Star in a Bottle}} provides a [[mana regeneration]] buff and is crafted with a [[Fallen Star]] and a [[Bottle]].
** '''Spawn rate Candles''': These [[Candles]] affect enemy/critter spawn rate within an area around them when placed or held.
*** The {{item|Water Candle}} increases enemy spawns and is found in the Dungeon, and can also be crafted.
*** The {{item|Peace Candle|icons=n}} decreases enemy spawns and is crafted with a [[Pink Torch]] and 2 [[Gold Bar|Gold]] or [[Platinum Bar]]s.
*** The {{item|Shadow Candle|icons=n}} allows enemy spawns in [[town]]s and is crafted with a [[Torch]] and 3 [[Demonite Bar|Demonite]] or [[Crimtane Bar]]s while in a [[Graveyard]].
** '''Decorative light sources''': These are decorative [[light sources]]. Some do not work as [[mechanisms]].
*** The {{item|Tiki Torch}} is crafted with a Torch and 3 of [[Any Wood]].
*** The {{item|Lamp Post}} is crafted with 3 of [[Any Iron Bar]], 2 [[Glass]], and a Torch.
*** The {{item|Skull Lantern}} is crafted from [[Bone]] and a Torch and also found in the [[Dungeon]].
*** The {{item|Chinese Lantern}} is an extra large lantern and is crafted using a Torch and 5 [[Silk]].
*** The {{item|Lava Lamp|icons=n}} and the {{item|Plasma Lamp|icons=n}} can be purchased from the [[Party Girl]] for {{iteminfo|Lava Lamp|buy}}.
* '''Tables''': In addition to the [[tables]] listed above, there are also Picnic Tables.
** The {{item|Picnic Table|icons=n}} is crafted with 12 of Any Wood.
** The {{item|Fancy Picnic Table|icons=n}} is crafted with 12 of Any Wood and 3 Silk.
* '''Toilets''': In addition to the [[Toilets]] listed above, there are two other Toilets that are not part of any set.
** The {{item|Diamond Toilet|icons=n}} is crafted using 6 [[Diamond]]s.
** The {{item|Terra Toilet|icons=n}} is crafted using a regular Toilet and a [[Broken Hero Sword]].

== Trivia ==
* The Solar, Nebula, Vortex, and Stardust furniture sets all have identical forms and only differ in color.
* While most furniture sets require the basic [[Torch]] to craft light items, the [[Boreal Wood furniture]] set and [[Frozen furniture]] set require a different type, the [[Ice Torch]].

